		<div class="post-2896 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-design category-quilting category-seder-masochism" id="post-2896">


<div class="post-headline">		<h2>			
			<a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2013/01/30/this-quilt-is-mine/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to This Quilt Is Mine">This Quilt Is Mine</a></h2>
		</div>

<div class="post-bodycopy clearfix"><p>My <em><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2012/10/01/this-land-is-mine/" target="_blank">This Land Is Mine</a></em> fabric (see <a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2013/01/11/canaan-quilt/">this post</a>) finally arrived from <a href="http://www.spoonflower.com/" target="_blank">Spoonflower</a>. I quilted it and hung it on the wall.</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/TLIM_white1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-2897" title="TLIM_white1" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/TLIM_white1-640x640.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="640" /></a></p>
<p>I ordered one version with a white background, and one with a dark background.</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/TLIM_dark4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-2898" title="TLIM_dark4" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/TLIM_dark4-640x640.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="640" /></a></p>
<p>Spoonflower does a great job printing colors, but the darks get muddy. The navy/grey background was indistinguishable from the black details. Sewing outlines in white thread helped, but I still prefer the white background.</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/TLIM_dark1.jpg"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-2899 alignleft" title="TLIM_dark1" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/TLIM_dark1-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/TLIM_dark2.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-2901" title="TLIM_dark2" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/TLIM_dark2-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/TLIM_dark3.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-2902" title="TLIM_dark3" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/TLIM_dark3-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/TLIM_white21.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-2903" title="TLIM_white2" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/TLIM_white21-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/TLIM_white4.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-2905" title="TLIM_white4" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/TLIM_white4-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/TLIM_white5.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-2906" title="TLIM_white5" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/TLIM_white5-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/TLIM_white6.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-2907" title="TLIM_white6" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/TLIM_white6-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a></p>
<div class="plus-one-wrap"><g:plusone href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2013/01/30/this-quilt-is-mine/"></g:plusone></div><div class="addtoany_share_save_container"><div class="a2a_kit a2a_kit_size_32 a2a_target addtoany_list" id="wpa2a_17"><a class="a2a_dd addtoany_share_save" href="http://www.addtoany.com/share_save" style="background:url(http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/plugins/add-to-any/favicon.png) no-repeat scroll 4px 0px !important;padding:0 0 0 25px;display:inline-block;height:16px;vertical-align:middle">Share/Bookmark</a></div></div><p class="wp-flattr-button"><a class="FlattrButton" style="display:none;" href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2013/01/30/this-quilt-is-mine/" title=" This Quilt Is Mine" rev="flattr;uid:ninapaley;language:en_GB;category:text;tags:blog;button:compact;">My This Land Is Mine fabric (see this post) finally arrived from Spoonflower. I quilted it and hung it on the wall. I ordered one version with a white background, and one with...</a></p></div>

